==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quicksand
<hw>Quick"sand`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Sand easily moved
or readily yielding to pressure; especially, a deep mass of loose or
moving sand mixed with water, sometimes found at the mouth of a river or
along some coasts, and very dangerous, from the difficulty of
extricating a person who begins sinking into it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Life hath <qex>quicksands</qex>, -- Life hath snares!</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1178 --></p>

<p><ent>Quick-scented</ent>⟦br⟧
